RuntimeError: got Future attached to a different loop

This is the classic async + prefork incompatibility. The fix is to not create the engine at module level and instead create it per asyncio.run() call, OR switch Celery to use the solo pool. Let me look at the scan_tasks.py and fix the fundamental architecture issue.

